==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Observation post
<hw>Ob`ser*va"tion post</hw>. <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>a military outpost,
usually at a height above the surrounding terrain, at or near the front
line of a battle from which an observer may see the enemy's positions
and direct artillery fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Observative</ent>⟦br⟧
